@node Installation "Installation"

First make sure you have installed the @{"ClassAct" link ClassAct} BOOPSI classes.
To install ASokoban from scratch or to update an old version just run the
installation script. (The script requires Commodore's Installer to run. If
you don't have it, it can be found on aminet).

If you install ASokoban 3 in the same location as an old version (i.e. 2.x)
your old score file will be converted to a new format when the game is run.

You can still use old data files, but you might want to rename them, since
the name of the data file also becomes the name of your player. You are
advised to place any data files into your chosen @{"Save directory" link ToolTypes}.

@endnode


@node Requirements "System Requirements"

ASokoban will run on any Amiga computer with version 2.0 or higher of the OS
(or at least I hope it will).

If you have version 2.1 or higher ASokoban will try to use the @{"language" link Localization} you
have selected through Preferences.

ASokoban requires the @{"ClassAct" link ClassAct} BOOPSI classes.

@endnode


