@node Game "The Game"

Sokoban is Japanese for Warehouse keeper. The purpose of the game is to
push all the packets through the maze into the safe. You can ONLY push
the packets - you can't pull them, pick them up or in any other way
manipulate them. Once all the packets are in the safe you proceed to the
next level. There is no time limit (you can sit all day trying to solve a
level). If you have already solved a level you can try to solve it again -
this time with less moves and pushes (there is a highscore entry for
every level). 

You can move your man with either the cursor keys or the mouse. The left
mouse button moves the man to the location you click at without making
any pushes. The right mouse button pushes the closest adjacent packet
to the location you clicked at. The middle mouse button undoes your last
move.

@endnode


@node Gadgets "The Gadgets"

@{b}Set Level...@{ub}
Pops up a requester that lets you choose which level to play. Note that
you can only play a level if you have finnished the preceding level.

@{b}Restart@{ub}
Restarts the current level.

@{b}Undo@{ub}
Undoes your last move. You can use this to undo as many moves as you like
(if you have enough memory).

@{b}Redo@{ub}
Undoes undo.

@{b}Backup@{ub}
Make a temporary snapshot of the current level.

@{b}Restore@{ub}
Brings back the last snapshot made.

@{b}High Scores...@{ub}
Shows the best results on the current level.

@{b}About...@{ub}
Shows version information and @{"ARexx" link ARexx} portname.

@endnode


@node Menu "The Menu"

@{b}Project@{ub}
	
	@{b}New...@{ub}
	Create a new player. A requester asks for the name of the player.
	
	@{b}Open...@{ub}
	Open a saved player.
	
	@{b}Save@{ub}
	Save the current player.
	
	@{b}High Scores...@{ub}
	Shows the best results on the current level.
	
	@{b}About...@{ub}
	Shows version information and @{"ARexx" link ARexx} portname.
	
	@{b}Quit ASokoban...@{ub}
	Quits the game.

@{b}Macros@{ub}
	
	@{b}Start Learning@{ub}
	Starts learning macro. Any user activity that has an @{"ARexx" link ARexx} command
	will be recorded.
	
	@{b}Stop Learning@{ub}
	Stops learing macro.
	
	@{b}Assign Macro...@{ub}
	Lets you save the current macro to disk.

@endnode


@node ARexx "ARexx Commands"

@{b}WALKTO@{ub}
	ROW/N/A,COL=COLUMN/N/A
Moves the man to the given location without making any pushes.

@{b}PUSHTO@{ub}
	ROW/N/A,COL=COLUMN/N/A
Pushes the closest adjacent packet to the given location.

@{b}MOVE@{ub}
	UP/S,DOWN/S,LEFT/S,RIGHT/S
Moves the man in the given direction.

@{b}SETLEVEL@{ub}
	/N
Sets the current level.

@{b}GETLEVEL@{ub}
	,
Returns the number of the current level in 'result'.

@{b}RESTART@{ub}
	,
Restarts the current level.

@{b}UNDO@{ub}
	/N
Undoes the last move, or if a number is given the "n" last moves.

@{b}REDO@{ub}
	/N
Undoes undo ("n" times if a number is given).

@{b}BACKUP@{ub}
	,
Makes a temporary snapshot of the current level.

@{b}RESTORE@{ub}
	,
Restores the last snapshot made.

@endnode


@node ToolTypes "Startup Arguments"

The following arguments are recognized both as CLI arguments and WB
ToolTypes.

@{b}PLAYER@{ub}
Name of player to open at startup.

@{b}LEVEL/N/K@{ub}
Startlevel.

@{b}IMAGEPATH/K@{ub}
Directory with images to use. Default is Images/original.

@{b}LEVELPATH/K@{ub}
Directory with levels to use. Default is Levels.

@{b}SAVEPATH/K@{ub}
Save directory.

@{b}PUBSCREEN/K@{ub}
Name of public screen to open ASokoban on.

@{b}LANGUAGE/K@{ub}
Language to use with ASokoban.

@endnode


@node History "Version History"

(v1.0a - v1.1c by Panagiotis Christias)
1.0a    : First stable version. Distributed among my friends only for beta
          testing.

1.0b    : First official release.

1.1     : Compiled with SAS C 6.1 using Reqtools.library 2.1. Undo bug fixed
          (found it myself!). Now ASokoban saves its position  automatically
          on exit ( reported by Kriton Kyrimis ) . Level 15  bug fixed , now
          ASokoban  counts as saved  packets which are  in the safe from the
          beginning of a level (like level 15 ) . First reported by  Carsten
          Steger . When  loading a datafile  maxlevel won't decrease if max-
          level of datafile is smaller than  current maxlevel . Suggested by
          Sebastian Delmont.

1.1c    : ASokoban used to have some problems  when finishing a level  using 
          the mouse . Bug is fixed , now  ASokoban  does not  lose any IDCMP 
          message ( reported by Markus Torpvret) .  This version of ASokoban
          supports any  kind ( and size ) of font  for the titlebar .  First
          reported by Terence Russell and Ives Aerts ( still Asokoban is not
          font sensitive, sorry...).

(Project taken over by Lorens Younes)
v2.0  (95-02-08) ASokoban is now fontsensitive (falls back to topaz 8 if the
                 graphics won't fit with the user prefered fonts).
                 Support for locale.library added.
                 Gadgets are now disabled when they have no function.
                 PUBSCREEN and DATAFILE tooltypes added.
                 New highscore list (one high score for each level instead of
                 an overall top ten).
                 Documentation in AmigaGuide format.
                 Installation script for Commodore's Installer.
                 ReqTools.library no longer used for requesters
                 (asl filerequester used instead).
v2.1  (95-02-25) ASokoban will no longer crash you system if the number of
                 moves exceed 9999 (reported by Jouni Jääskeläinen).
                 Zoom gadget (re)added on Panagiotis Christias' "demand" ;-)
v2.2  (95-03-01) Now ASokoban correctly handles translated gadget labels
                 without an undersore (reported by Uwe Röhm).
v2.3  (95-05-27) Undo no longer causes system failure under AmigaOS 2.x (first
                 reported by Fredrik Hällgren who also solved the problem for
                 me).
                 Five more levels included from xsokoban.
v2.4  (95-06-05) Bug that caused some strange text to appear over the name
                 gadget fixed (reported by Niels Knoop).
v2.5  (95-07-06) Added LANGUAGE tooltype (requested by Niels Goers).
v2.6  (95-07-17) Fixed layout bug that occured when using fonts with height
                 less then 8 pixels (reported by Lauri Aalto).
v2.7b (95-08-??) Version only released to beta-testers. It used XPM images to
                 get colorfull graphics, but it was very slow!

v3.0  (96-08-11) A completly rewritten version. Major new features are
                 ARexx support, external graphic files (XPM format),
                 external level files (text), unlimited undo, improved
                 mouse support and improved handling of data files (players).
                 Also, ASokoban now uses the ClassAct GUI toolkit.
v3.1  (96-11-19) Fixed problem with large fonts.

@endnode


